---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Pest Control Edmonton | Cockroaches, Ants, Termites"
  description="Pest control in Edmonton, Cairns — general pest, cockroaches, ants, rodents and termites for the southern growth corridor. Year-round tropical protection, recurring plans, free quote."
  canonical="https://cairnspestmanagement.com.au/edmonton/">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Edmonton &middot; Mount Sheridan &middot; Bentley Park &middot; southern corridor</span>
      <h1>Pest control in <span class="accent">Edmonton</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Edmonton is the southern growth corridor of Cairns &mdash; a busy mix of
        new estate homes and established stock between the highway and the ranges.
        In this tropical climate cockroaches and ants are a year-round battle, the
        wet season brings rodents indoors, and termites stay active twelve months
        of the year. We treat the lot and offer recurring plans so it stays sorted.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Edmonton</span>
      <h2>Pest control for the southern corridor.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>New estates and established homes, same tropical pressure.</h3>
        <p>
          Edmonton, Mount Sheridan and Bentley Park have grown fast, so we see two
          kinds of home here &mdash; brand-new estate builds and older established
          stock &mdash; and both cop the same wet-tropics pest load. New homes are
          not immune: fresh landscaping, mulch and turf bring ants and cockroaches
          straight in, and a builder&rsquo;s termite barrier still needs annual
          inspection to stay valid. Older Edmonton homes near the ranges add the
          usual mix of sub-floor harbourage and garden-edge ant trails.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Cockroaches and ants run all year.</h3>
        <p>
          The two pests Edmonton calls about most are <strong>cockroaches and
          ants</strong>. With no winter to knock them back, German and American
          cockroaches breed continuously around kitchens, bins and sub-floors,
          and coastal brown and black house ants march in from fresh garden beds
          and slab edges. We treat with targeted gel baits plus a low-odour
          residual barrier, and because the breeding never stops, a recurring
          plan is the practical fix &mdash; see
          <a href="/services/cockroach-ant-control/">cockroach &amp; ant control</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Wet-season rodents and active termites.</h3>
        <p>
          When the rains arrive, rats and mice head indoors and into roof voids
          across the corridor &mdash; we bait safely and seal the entry points
          (<a href="/services/rodent-control/">rodent control</a>). And termites
          never take a break here: Edmonton sits in the range of both Coptotermes
          and the giant northern Mastotermes, so every home, new or old, should
          have an annual <a href="/services/termite-control/">termite
          inspection</a> to AS&nbsp;3660 &mdash; especially new builds keeping their
          barrier warranty alive.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Edmonton jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>General pest treatment on a new estate home &mdash; cockroaches, ants, spiders, 12-month warranty (~$250&ndash;$320)</li>
          <li>Recurring 6 or 12-monthly protection plan for an established family home</li>
          <li>German cockroach clean-out in an Edmonton kitchen with follow-up included (~$215&ndash;$290)</li>
          <li>Wet-season rodent baiting and roof-void proofing (~$180&ndash;$350)</li>
          <li>AS 3660 annual termite inspection to keep a new-build barrier warranty valid (~$235&ndash;$380)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/smithfield/">Smithfield</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/redlynch/">Redlynch</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/trinity-beach/">Trinity Beach</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/earlville/">Earlville</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cairns-region/">All Cairns Region</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Edmonton pest control quote.</h2>
        <p>General pest, cockroaches, ants, rodents and termites. Recurring plans for year-round protection.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
